title: Ask HN: Google double charged me for 5y, agreed for partial refund. Whats next?
text:
Just got response from Google Workspace support, they can only refund for the last 6 months:

"I am glad to inform you that our internal team granted our refund request for 6 months worth of Google Drive subscription. I tried to request for more than 6 months but this is the maximum that they can provide."

So last 5 years they charged me for Google Workspace which includes google drive and at the same time separately for google drive. Case closed, problem (for them) solved.

Really? What will you advice to do next ?

Ask HN: Are we sure LLMs are that useful in a web search application?
text:
Idly chatting with the search box doesn't strike me as the most productive use of my time.

Instant answers or whatever they're called already produce direct answers plus they cite sources and provide links which is what everyone seems to think is the solution to the "LLMs make stuff up" problem.

Not to mention they're faster and cheaper to run.

Only truly practical use case I can think of is summarizing articles or writing them which makes more sense as a word processor or browser add-ons

Ask HN: Is AI the next (current) dot-com era?
text:
I am old enough to remember the dot-com era, and actually I worked at one of those high-flying innovative dot-com, while we didn't make it, technologically speaking we changed the world as we knew it for >10 years after that.

Anyway.

ChatCPT and other first gen AI-apps have surpassed all of my expectations, and this is just the beginning.

I feel like this is the beginning of a wave of innovation, with its ramification, just like we experienced in the dot-com era.

What does HN think?

Show HN: Supertweak – Chrome extension to easily tweak Tailwind websites live
text:
Hey everyone, I've made a chrome extension that makes designing and building Tailwind websites much simpler and faster.

It let's you quickly tweak your website right inside the browser and copy back classes or html to your editor afterwards. As a developer who designs with code, I personally find it very useful in iterating on design quickly without any context switching.

Please give it a try and let me know what you think!

website: https://supertweak.dev

https://derdiedas.wtf/: Pain of understanding the gender of nouns in German
text:
Just release the v2 of https://derdiedas.wtf/

German language and its rules are hard. Specially the gender of noun. This is my attempt to make life a bit easier for those learning German.

Total 2807 nouns added. Right now we have 210 nouns and levels up to B1.2, The lists are updated every few weeks from the initial list of 2807 nouns and gender. You can opt to receive email when new list of nouns are added.
